column1: 89006;instagram;2019-01-05 20:19:14;FALSE;"this week has been hard. jazmine barnes
column5: and the public’s response to the surviving r. kelly series has drained me like dishwater.  it’s emerging that jazmine’s murder might have been racially motivated. r. kelly has been allowed to thrive and prey on black underage girls by his fans and his entourage for three decades.  both of these things happened because no one is coming to run and save black girls from hateful and powerful men and the poison they knowingly place in our lives.

column1: r. kelly lured in so many girls and some have emerged as bruised and hurt women with their life chances and dreams altered. whatever aspirations jazmine barnes had for her life will never come to pass. i can’t even imagine if she was old enough to ponder whether she wanted to be a doctor or a dancer or an astronaut. i’m angry. i don’t think a time will come to pass that i won’t be angry about how the world constantly shows that it is natural for black girls and women to bear the brunt of this country’s hatred.
so because i choose not to yell about everything that upsets me: i bought this book for my nieces. i want them to have a reference to women in history that look like them and to be proud of and maybe
column2: see the possibilities of what their life could be. they’re too young to know how to tie their shoes
column3: let alone what to do with their lives. but the thought of their pride and happiness makes me feel better. something that also made me feel better was rep. lauren underwood (of illinois) being sworn in this week as the youngest black congresswoman. in the midst of my anger and annoyance with this world

column1: 89017;instagram;2019-01-05 20:27:02;FALSE;"heroes - have you ever stopped to think about what makes a hero and why we love them so much? 🤔
i don’t think it has as much to do with the triumphant endings as most of us might assume. i think it’s more about watching a person stumble
column3: take two steps forward then one step back
column8: gain resilience and belief in self
column9: then and only then ultimately persevere. it’s less about the end and more about the lessons we learn through them was they fail time and time again on their journey. 🗺 .

column1: point being - heroes don’t get to be heroes without failing more times than they actually win. 💥
#truthbomb - make the lessons of failure your friend
column2: so you aren’t stuck in the cycle of repeating the the same failures over and over again. 💣

column1: 89028;instagram;2019-01-05 20:40:08;FALSE;"i watched surviving r. kelly and i was disturbed by the things said. i survived sexual abuse and domestic violence and my stomach dropped after hearing every woman recanting their story. it then took me back to the many people who posted on social media that said they sound like liars.

it triggered memories  to when i became vocal with my abuse that i received the same judgement that drove me to depression and cause me not to value life. i listened to every single woman that had something to say. you think andrea kelly is lying? research her kids and you see how they are coping? you think sparkle is lying? when was the last time she has dropped an album? she was black balled.
in the world of an abuser
column2: power and money speak volumes. in this case money played a big part.

column1: we live in a world that women are continuously scared to come out and be open about their abuse because of the backlash that comes with it. this is why the abuser continues to manipulate and continue the cycle of abuse. survivors and victims who come forward are soooo brave because they have to relieve their shame and hurt.

i find it awkward that the people that are throwing stones haven't endured this kind of pain. this clearly shows a reflection of who you are and where you came from.. #365daysofdomesticviolence #sexualabuseisreal #survivorsarestrong #survivingrkelly #spiritsarereal #metoo #nomoresilence #speakup #itstime #iamasurvivor #sexualabuse #rape #molestation

column2: i used to talk to boys; drive motor cycles
column3: smoke cigarettes and people in bandra would often call me a whore because of those things. i never understood the term back then
column4: but sure if doing all those things made me a whore-- i'd take it gladly. after my father’s death
column5: i moved to chicago where there were so many like me and it gave me the freedom to get inked
column6: experiment with my hair and just be myself. one christmas eve in chicago
column7: i walked out of a bar alone late at night in a short dress and red lipstick. i was 24 and had been drinking
column8: when from a dumpster a group of guys walked upto me and put a gun to my head asking me to give them blow jobs
column9: eventually leading to gang rape. i remember walking home
column10: showering and pushing this incident to the back of my mind for years and never letting it break my spirit – i still wear short dresses and the brightest red on my lips.

column2: i got married to my high school sweetheart
column3: faced domestic violence and walked out of the marriage wondering how this could happen to me
column4: a feminist? it’s because sometimes there are things that are beyond your control. we live in a world where everyone stresses the importance of voicing yourself or walking out of tough situations
column5: but i just want to say this— no one wants to be beaten up
column6: get raped or sell their bodies. it took me 20 years to voice my incident
column7: but for me a woman keeping it all within her because she has no other choice isn’t a sign of weakness – it’s a mark of strength and something we need to start respecting.”

column1: 89107;instagram;2019-01-05 19:22:52;FALSE;"i have a little history lesson on my boxing journey. i started out as a dancer
column2: those of you who know me know that dance was my life. i lived and breathed the dance studio. but about two
column3: two and a half (i honestly try to forget) years ago
column4: someone assaulted me. it wasn’t violent. i wasn’t injured or bruised. but someone put power over me and even after repeated “no” and “i don’t want to” they got what they wanted from me anyways. that feeling of being so helpless and powerless over myself and my body shut me down for months...months. no dancing
column5: no exercising. i just existed. then my trainer dug me out of that hole and taught me how to defend myself. he has given me the strength not only physically but mentally to handle anything. and i honestly encourage everyone to take on a combat sport. you never know what could happen in this world. and having something to defend myself has given me so much confidence and pride that i can take on any obstacle💕💕

column1: thank you @innerstrength_ts again for freeing me and my mind to be whatever i want to be💪🏼🥊 .

column1: 89109;instagram;2019-01-05 19:24:39;FALSE;"haft några tunga veckor. men sedan nyår ungefär verkar det som att jag nästintill tappat fotfästet helt.
jag kämpar för en balans i livet. jag kämpar med att lyssna på kroppen och hjärnan. jag kämpar med att inte hamna för långt ner i den negativa spiralen.
hur får man ens allt det att gå ihop? hur får man det att fungera?

column3: kunna mer. vara mer ""normal"". men det finns så många farthinder och snubbeltrådar. jag vet inte ens var jag ska börja. med vad jag ska börja.

column1: jag börjar falla farligt djupt. jag har trillat ner så gott som alla pinnhål jag hade klättrat upp. jag vågar/orkar inte gå ut. jag har otroligt svårt att behålla maten. jag vill inte vara vaken. vaken betyder tankar och känslor som jag inte vet var jag ska göra av.
jag slåss med att våga be om närhet och tröst
column2: och att rida ut stormarna själv. jag känner mig ständigt i vägen och till besvär. otillräcklig på så många vis. inte bara gentemot min sambo utan även gentemot mig själv. jag blir besviken på att jag tillåter mig själv dyka på det här viset. att jag inte kämpar mer. kämpar hårdare.

column1: jag skulle vilja skriva något positivt. hur bra det går. vilka framsteg jag gör och allt sådant.
men jag misstänker att jag åkt på ett rejält bakslag helt enkelt. vilket visserligen är helt naturligt och en del i processen. eller ja

idag är det tre år sedan. det borde inte påverka mig längre och jag förstår inte vad det är för fel på mig som gör att det fortfarande påverkar mig. omständigheterna kring hela grejen? allt som kom fram efteråt? tankarna som dyker upp tillsammans med situationen som var då? kedjereaktion tankemässigt? hur allt överhuvudtaget var både innan
column2: då och efter det? misstanken om att det faktiskt var en våldtäkt som trots allt ledde till det hela? skammen kring hur blåögd och dum jag var? jag vill bara glömma. skära ut de minnena. de som har med det och honom att göra. låta det försvinna i intet. sluta låta det påverka mig. #psykiskohälsa #våldtäkt #metoo #komplexptsd #cptsd #bipolar #bipolärsjukdom #trauma #depression #ångest #mardrömmar #detgårattblibättre #sexuelltvåld #psykiskmisshandel #osynligmisshandel";;en;#psykiskohälsa

column830: och att rida ut stormarna själv . jag känner mig ständigt vägen och till besvär . otillräcklig på så många vi . inte bara gentemot min sambo utan även gentemot mig själv . jag blir besviken på att jag tillåter mig själv dyka på det här viset . att jag inte kämpar mer . kämpar hårdare . jag skulle vilja skriva något positivt . hur bra det går . vilka framsteg jag gör och allt sådant . men jag misstänker att jag åkt på ett rejält bakslag helt enkelt . vilket visserligen är helt naturligt och en del processen . eller ja
column831: alla processer . idag är det tre år sedan . det borde inte påverka mig längre och jag förstår inte vad det är för fel på mig som gör att det fofarande påverkar mig . omständigheterna kring hela grejen ? allt som kom fram efteråt ? tankarna som dyker upp tillsammans med situationen som var då ? kedjereaktion tankemässigt ? hur allt överhuvudtaget var både

column1: 89304;instagram;2019-01-05 16:35:13;FALSE;"#linkinbio trigger warning: “lifetime’s rendering of kelly’s story does not excavate unreported rumors with an eye trained uncritically toward salacious gossip. rather
column2: the documentary brings together the previously reported but nonetheless disturbing accounts of his accusers—and indicts the many people who have enabled his alleged abuses with their silence. through its attention to overlapping patterns in the women’s accusations and in the social systems that fail young black girls and women
column3: surviving r. kelly repeatedly makes an almost impossibly simple observation: the singer’s alleged history of systematized predation could not have occurred without a ready network of support (https://bit.ly/2tpc49s).”

column1: 89328;instagram;2019-01-05 14:45:09;FALSE;"the good life  i had always envisioned 2 kids (boy and girl) and a loving husband. and when penny came into the world
for a time in my life
column2: i struggled with depression. i had a very low view of myself and felt i was not worth anything. i allowed the people around me to keep me feeling like this. i was a 100% people pleaser
column3: even if it meant sacrificing my integrity. and when i was not true to myself
column4: i felt even worse about myself.

column2: and has very serious effects on all parts of life. thankfully
column3: i recognized i needed help and got into therapy. no shame! while working with my therapist
column4: i learned a lot about myself. i discovered that i was worth it! i had so much worth
column5: and yet i was not respecting it by staying where i was.

column2: right time  i was offered a job
column3: states away from everyone and everything i knew. i'd be closer to my brother
column4: but everything else would be new. so
column5: i took it! i left behind the old ""worthless"" me and started a new life in a new place.

column1: everything has changed! and my dreams came true. now
column2: i do still manage my depression. it's something i am always aware of. but i know how strong and full of worth i am. and i know that i can overcome anything.

i am sure to (try) to get 7+ hours of sleep (kids effect this one). and i surround myself with positive people. and i have daily sessions... but not with a therapist. i workout! i sweat and challenge myself to do better (almost) every day. i am encouraged by super trainers
column4: and i feel so much better every time i get done.

column1: you are not alone. if you are fighting depression
column2: addiction or any other psychological or physical problems
column3: you are not alone! find your people
column4: connect and be empowered by each other! you are not alone.  your dreams are worth it

column1: for a time in my life
column2: i struggled with depression. i had a very low view of myself and felt i was not woh anything. i allowed the people around me to keep me feeling like this. i was a 100% people pleaser
column3: even if it meant sacrificing my integrity. and when i was not true to myself
column4: i felt even worse about myself.

column2: and has very serious effects on all pas of life. thankfully
column3: i recognized i needed help and got into therapy. no shame! while working with my therapist
column4: i learned a lot about myself. i discovered that i was woh it! i had so much woh
column5: and yet i was not respecting it by staying where i was.

column2: right time  i was offered a job
column3: states away from everyone and everything i knew. i'd be closer to my brother
column4: but everything else would be new. so
column5: i took it! i left behind the old ""wohless"" me and staed a new life in a new place.

column1: everything has changed! and my dreams came true. now
column2: i do still manage my depression. it is something i am always aware of. but i know how strong and full of woh i am. and i know that i can overcome anything.

i am sure to (try) to get 7+ hours of sleep (kids effect this one). and i surround myself with positive people. and i have daily sessions... but not with a therapist. i workout! i sweat and challenge myself to do better (almost) every day. i am encouraged by super trainers
column4: and i feel so much better every time i get done.

column2: i am not a fan of the man and his actions. listening to the accusations levelled by @jerhonda4pace disturbed me to my core. her story resonated with me the most. i could not believe what i was hearing. i feel for her and all of the ladies impacted by kelly's alleged actions. we have to stop shunning black women when they share their stories or thinking they are liars who just want to ""bring a good man down."" we need to stop putting these goddamned celebrities on a pedestal and we need to stop putting a wall of protection around predators.

“just because something has been done for generations doesn’t mean it’s right. many of our grandparents or parents back in the day dated wayyyyy older men and it was normalized
column2: but this really isn’t okay. there are too many young girls currently dating men twice their age. the hood glamorizes the hell out of these older men and younger girls relationships
column6: 16 year olds dating men in their 20’s its not okay!!!!!!!!!! we have to stop defending dysfunction. please talk to your daughters about appropriate age gaps when dating. there are some men who prey on young girls
column7: especially girls who lack things (i.e-bonds with their mother or father
column8: a safe haven to go to
column9: lack of family attachment etc). then you have all of these urban fiction love/hood stories that pre-teens and teenagers have access to reading the pages of the book so caught up in fairytales
column10: promoting these type of lifestyles. this is real life people. i myself can remember reading the “coldest winter ever” when i was no more than 12-13years old
column11: probably even younger than that😩 and thinking i myself
column12: was going to have some older man come save me and be my “midnight” due to the lack of attachment i felt at home . reflecting back on it now i know better but many of our young black girls don’t. so if you can help and save them from this please have open and honest conversations regarding this topic.dont shoot me i’m just the messenger. just ask yourself this....would it be appropriate for a 13 year old boy to be with a 25 year old woman? noooooo so why is it okay for our young girls? #unpopularopinion #dating #preteens #blackgirls #parenting #predators #urbanfiction #metoo #inappropriate #mentalillness #selfcare #discussion #foodforthought #unlearn #relearn #rape  #depression #ptsd #bipolar #mentalillness #blackwoman #therapyforblackgirls #breakpoint #survivingrkelly";;en;#UnPopularOpinion

column1: this is ayanna pressley (@yaa nnapressley)  the new congresswoman for massachusetts’ 7th congressional district and the first black woman elected to congress from massachusetts and my nominee for people’s most beautiful person of the year. •
one of the problems i’ve faced in the past election cycle is being swept up by so many different groundbreaking and historic moments
column2: that i’ve failed to look at the incredible policies and plans of these new women lawmakers. i do think it’s important
column3: especially when we are subject to media soundbites that we take the time to learn about each of these icons
column4: outside of them being the “first” of something. so
column5: i’ve decided to educate myself with the help of google to learn more about the political stances of these incredible and progressive women. •

column1: ayanna pressley supports the “take a knee” practice which is used to bring attention to police brutality towards black men. congresswoman pressley supports medicare for all and has called for the defunding of ice. she has also been a supporter of the #metoo movement and has vocalized her support for impeachment of donald trump. •

column1: 89425;instagram;2019-01-05 14:54:07;FALSE;"i haven’t watched surviving r. kelly yet. however
column2: i always knew the man had issues from years ago when he married aaliyah and then when the sex tape came out showing him with a minor. i’ve never understood why people didn’t believe it then. fast forward to recent when the news came out about women being held in his atlanta home. also there is an old video of r. kelly being interviewed and i remember him saying to the pastor that he needed help. so do i believe he did all of these things absolutely. when things like this come out you really see the true heart of people and it’s sad that so many people are poking fun or blaming the victims. as a survivor of sexual abuse there is no statue of limitations on the symptoms you experience from being abused. it’s something you live with the rest of your life and you learn to cope as best you can. i’m sick of hearing people say that  happened many years ago as if that justifies anything. most people don’t tell until years later because of the shame attached and because people don’t believe the victim. it’s so many people walking around who haven’t told. we wonder why so many people abuse drugs and alcohol or why people have sexual addictions and on and on. chances are they were abused sexually. i’m pretty sure r. kelly experienced sexual abuse himself. now this is not an excuse it’s an explanation. this thing has been going on for some long in all communities and everyone wants to keep it hush
column3: hush. it’s one of the reasons i started @mygirlsinc. kudos to the women for speaking out and telling their stories because it takes a lot of courage to do so.

column1: 89428;instagram;2019-01-05 14:54:54;FALSE;"i haven’t watched surviving r. kelly yet. however
column2: i always knew the man had issues from years ago when he married aaliyah and then when the sex tape came out showing him with a minor. i’ve never understood why people didn’t believe it then. fast forward to recent when the news came out about women being held in his atlanta home. also there is an old video of r. kelly being interviewed and i remember him saying to the pastor that he needed help. so do i believe he did all of these things absolutely. when things like this come out you really see the true heart of people and it’s sad that so many people are poking fun or blaming the victims. as a survivor of sexual abuse there is no statue of limitations on the symptoms you experience from being abused. it’s something you live with the rest of your life and you learn to cope as best you can. i’m sick of hearing people say that  happened many years ago as if that justifies anything. most people don’t tell until years later because of the shame attached and because people don’t believe the victim. it’s so many people walking around who haven’t told. we wonder why so many people abuse drugs and alcohol or why people have sexual addictions and on and on. chances are they were abused sexually. i’m pretty sure r. kelly experienced sexual abuse himself. now this is not an excuse it’s an explanation. this thing has been going on for some long in all communities and everyone wants to keep it hush
column3: hush. it’s one of the reasons i started @mygirlsinc. kudos to the women for speaking out and telling their stories because it takes a lot of courage to do so.

column1: 89431;instagram;2019-01-05 14:56:27;TRUE;;"i was on my way & then it happened
column2: it all came to a halt. i broke my right foot & my world stopped moving
column3: literally. the bad voices started to creep in & soon after
column4: the darkness moved back in. however
column5: one thing is different. the light

column1: our thoughts shape who we are
it’s the crisis the trials & tribulations that help form who you are. i’m changed & continue to change

i desire is to strive to be better than who i allowed myself to be molded into. i can no longer blame the years for having a bad one or for bad things happening. life isn’t fair at times & that isn’t always easy
column2: especially watching friends or family suffer in pain and agony. if i stay here in the darkness
column4: i will slowly kill my soul.

column1: you will be transformed by the renewing of your mind so
what your speak out of your mouth 👄 is what will change your life

column2: thought and habits with something good
column3: just retrain and exchange the bad for the good
column4: discipline yourself & soon your world will change
column5: inside as well as out! and most importantly remember it’s ok to start over from scratch

you will survive and you are victorious not a victim!!

o conto da aia foi escrito há mais de 30 anos pela premiada autora canadense margaret atwood. porém
column2: nunca se ouviu falar tanto na obra como nos últimos meses. a eleição de donald trump para presidência dos eua
column3: o surgimento de movimentos como o #metoo
column4: a campanha eleitoral bem como as falas de algumas figuras políticas brasileiras
column5: o lançamento da série baseada no livro
column6: foram alguns dos principais motivos que fizeram com que as vendas de exemplares da obra disparassem a ponto dela se tornar presença constante na lista de livros mais vendidos desde 2017.

column1: ler ""o conto da aia"" não foi tarefa fácil
column2: pois foi uma leitura angustiante do início ao fim. todos os meus medos enquanto mulher estão aqui representados e saber que a autora se baseou em fatos históricos para os detalhes desta narrativa só serviu para aumentar a minha tensão. no entanto
column3: mesmo não despertando sentimentos muito agradáveis
column4: essa foi minha melhor leitura do ano.

column1: abuse is about power and control. it’s a gendered phenomenon
column2: but that does not mean it doesn’t happen in queer communities. in fact - as queer communities & queer women we need to get much better at identifying unhealthy dynamics like isolation (ie by constantly being with someone during all activities) & gaslighting survivors when they speak out about charismatic individuals whose most controlling behaviour you will likely never have encountered personally & may seem absolutely unbelievable...🧐

column1: 89517;instagram;2019-01-05 13:18:56;FALSE;"release your pain from the past to live your best life

the #metoo women’s movement has recently shed light on the fact that many women have experienced trauma in their life. the pain of the past is real and we lock it away in our bodies & hearts everyday in order to survive. but this locked trauma can resurface as depression
get support for your healing journey

the revive & rise healing yoga retreat is your place and space to get on the mat and to do your work with the support of other women. this event is for you if you are absolutely ready to let go of what is no longer serving you
column2: to be free of your pain
column3: and to rise into the divine feminine goddess you know you are.

column3: this is a commitment to yourself and those around you that you care about
column4: that you are ready to fully step into your power and are ready to ask for help in doing so.

column2: и вы не знаете какого цвета купить сплюшку для малышки🤔
что цветовая гамма окружающих ребенка игрушек
column4: чтобы он развивал свои способности цветовосприятия👀. до шести месяцев малышу лучше всего покупать желтые💛
column5: красные❤ или зеленые игрушки💚. эти цвета воспринимаются в этом возрасте наиболее четко и привлекательно☝

column1: как же влияют разные цвета на детей?

column2: что этот радостный цвет укрепляет нервную систему и зрение. в школах часто красят стены в желтый цвет
column3: чтобы настроить учеников на положительный лад и снять их усталость.

column4: даже могут понизить температуру и замедлить распространение инфекции

column1: 🍇фиолетовый и сиреневый. это тоже успокаивающие цвета
column3: однако их избыток может привести к депрессии – поэтому стоит обратить внимание на душевное состояние ребенка
column4: если его тянет к данным тонам. не исключено
column6: которому нравится все фиолетовое и сиреневое
column7: испытавает душевный дискомфорт и ищет покоя.

column6: этот цвет может также казаться скучным и вгонять в тоску
column7: поэтому вокруг ребенка его не должно быть слишком много.

column4: стимулирует обмен веществ и сердечную активность. однако с этим цветом нужно быть осторожным – если его слишком много в жизни ребенка

column1: 🍊оранжевый. улучшает пищеварение и работу щитовидной железы
column2: полезен при проблемах с желудком и кишечником. по мнению диетологов

column1:
;сексуальный скандал на нобелевской премии 2018 ⠀ в 2018 году самая престижная премия в мире была сильно задета именно темой насилия . в предыдущих постах мы уже рассказали о премии мира , которую получили представители стран , в которых сексуальное насилие процветает . ⠀ но оказывается , домогательство имеет места везде , даже в шведской академии наук . ⠀ началось все с того , что 18 женщин обвинили в домогательствах видного культурного деятеля жан-клода арно , который , по их словам , делал это прямо в помещениях академии . все это либо сотрудницы академии , либо дочери или жены членов . 72-летнего фотографа признали виновным в изнасиловании , произошедшем в 2011 году , и приговорили к двум годам тюрьмы . арно все отрицает и обещает обжаловать приговор . ⠀ выяснилось , что через свою супругу он получал финансирование своих проектов из нобелевского фонда . катарина фростенсон член шведской академии , поэтесса и драматург . в академии отмечают , что она всегда агрессивно реагировала на вопросы . связанные с ее мужем . ⠀ в довершение арно сливал имена лауреатов до официального объявления . академия разорвала с ним все связи , но внутри организации начался кризис . у фростенсон осталось много друзей в академии , началась волна массовых отставок других членов академии , а потом все-таки ушла и сама фростенсон . ⠀ по уставу члены академии выбираются пожизненно , то есть пока они живы нельзя набрать других человек . но даже , чтобы выбрать нового академика после смерти действующего , необходим кворум из 12 голосов , а сейчас осталось всего 10 членов . ⠀ награда за 2018 год будет вручена в следующем году . то есть в 2019-м году назовут двух лауреатов . а пока в этом году создали альтернативную премию . в шорт-листе харуки мураками , нил гейман , мариз конде и ким тхюй . победителя назовут 12 октября . ⠀ движение скандалы в голливуде , премия мира связанная с насилием над женщинами , а теперь и академия , которая присуждает самую престижную награду , замешана в сексуальном скандале . остается надеяться , что с приданием всех этих дел огласке , проблемы с насилием будут удостоены большего внимания . ⠀ как вам такой поворот в 2018 ? ⠀ источник : помещениях академии . все это либо сотрудницы академии , либо дочери или жены членов . 72-летнего фотографа признали виновным в изнасиловании , произошедшем в 2011 году , и приговорили к двум годам тюрьмы . арно все отрицает и обещает обжаловать приговор . ⠀ выяснилось , что через свою супругу он получал финансирование своих проектов из нобелевского фонда . катарина фростенсон член шведской академии , поэтесса и драматург . в академии отмечают , что она всегда агрессивно реагировала на вопросы . связанные с ее мужем . ⠀ в довершение арно сливал имена лауреатов до официального объявления . академия разорвала с ним все связи , но внутри организации начался кризис . у фростенсон осталось много друзей в академии , началась волна массовых отставок других членов академии , а потом все-таки ушла и сама фростенсон . ⠀ по уставу члены академии выбираются пожизненно , то есть пока они живы нельзя набрать других человек . но даже , чтобы выбрать нового академика после смерти действующего , необходим кворум из 12 голосов , а сейчас осталось всего 10 членов . ⠀ награда за 2018 год будет вручена в следующем году . то есть в 2019-м году назовут двух лауреатов . а пока в этом году создали альтернативную премию . в шорт-листе харуки мураками , нил гейман , мариз конде и ким тхюй . победителя назовут 12 октября . ⠀ движение скандалы в голливуде , премия мира связанная с насилием над женщинами , а теперь и академия , которая присуждает самую престижную награду , замешана в сексуальном скандале . остается надеяться , что с приданием всех этих дел огласке , проблемы с насилием будут удостоены большего внимания . ⠀ как вам такой поворот в 2018 ? ⠀ источник : strana.ua , ria.ru , bbc.com;сексуальный скандал на нобелевской премии 2018 ⠀ в 2018 году самая престижная премия в мире column1: 89671;instagram;2019-01-05 09:00:16;FALSE;"as the year begins it is normal to think just because you did not make any or not all your goals and you are older now it's to late to achieve those goals again . but let me tell you god is not done with you yet. to make a foundation you need fine powdery cement but you need sand as well and gravel.

think of your disappointments and missed opportunities as the experience you need which are the gravel you need to make a solid foundation. and the taller the  building the deeper the foundation. so the question you should ask is what are you building? the second mistake we make is we are the architects so the building will always crumble. what we need is the architect of the universe to step in

column1: i'm reena .  i'm 16 years old and i too have the same dreams and aspirations just like you . but i know being a girl is not easy . people judge you everyday
column3: living in an unknown village from bengal i don't know how to write letters or read the news .  my neighbour's has a radio which is turned on throughout the day . i've heard a lot of stories about the women being raped in the clubs . the skirts the shot dresses always become the victims . living in a well educated society you people started a #metoo movement recently exposing the wrongs done to you !!!!

column1: let me tell you . i also had a story to share . we don't have any social media or any mode of communicating the world . we don't get the opportunity to share our stories instead we need to hide them . so let me speak out ... let me tell you it's not only the skirts
column2: the short dresses that  always become the victims of rape but the burkhas and salwar kameez all fall in the list !!!

column1: shhh.... don't tell to anyone . okay?? or else my abba will lock me up in a room again .  this should remain only between you and me . believe me the situation of the girls living in a village are lot more difficult .  last tuesday
column2: my seven year old sister was touched inappropriately
column4: my elder sister was physically assaulted . and last night
column5: suddenly all i found was my dad . i couldn't speak just because he put a cloth in my mouth
column6: tied my hands . i was screaming
column7: i could find my amma's voice outside the room . he pulled my clothes
column8: ohh god the blood oozed out
column10: i prayed . yet he didn't listen . he continued to use his manly power  and desires until he was done . i was left all alone in my room throughout the night .  next morning
column11: when i told my maa what happened last night
column12: she kept silent . all she said was ""tum ladki ho
column13: ye toh hoti hi"" take some pills !!!!

column1: 💫 one of the most memorable moments of time’s up in the uk for me has been the launch of the justice and equality fund (the uk’s version of the legal defence fund)
column2: which aims to support women who have experienced harassment and abuse
column4: and prevent future abuses from occurring. 💸 the jef offers much-needed funds to existing expert services and to grassroots activism. 🌱 many people don’t realise that very basic services which protect and care for women in the uk are under threat
column5: and it’s incredible the difference the fund has made in a short space of time. 🌷

column1: the justice and equality fund (jef) has already resourced the vital work of organisations like 💪🏾💗london black women's project
column2: who provide specialist support to women of colour and migrant survivors of abuse
column4: who will resource a free and confidential helpline led by women lawyers offering legal advice to women experiencing sexual harassment. ☎️❤️ the jef has also supported keeping the rape and sexual abuse support centre for england and wales helpline open and is resourcing the first rape crisis service provision in northern ireland in 12 years. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: ⭐️ i hope that more people will be inspired by the #timesup anniversary to give at home here in the uk
column2: so the justice and equality fund can reach even more under-resourced organisations and campaign groups in 2019.

column1: 89684;instagram;2019-01-05 07:26:03;FALSE;"this is probably going to rub some people the wrong way but try to remember this cute smile as you read. (because i'm going to say it anyway.) 😊 next christmas
column2: when you are preparing to put your child on the lap of a strange man in costume (santa)
column3: whether they seem happy to see him or they're screaming their lungs out
column4: reflect and remember how you (specifically the ladies) feel when/if you feel obligated to entertain men (of any age) who make you feel uncomfortable. consider whether or not what you are doing is initiating the cycle of forced interaction between your child and a strange man and if that picture will be worth the possible future anxiety that that brief moment could perpetuate. .

column3: i was thinking about screaming babies being forced to sit in santa's lap for the sake of getting a picture and it just irked me. i literally was visualizing children
column5: trying to stay away from him and their parents just laughing it off. and
column6: i wondered if they feel the way i have when i don't want to be bothered but am ""forced"" to a certain degree
column8: they can't speak and/or their vocabulary isn't vast enough to fully express their thoughts and emotions. all they have are their facial expressions and cries. let's just try to be more sensitive to their communication moving forward. maybe they know something we don't know. and more importantly
column11: let's commit to do that. that's all. xo

column1: p.s. i'm not telling you what to do with your child. this is just food for thought. 💖

column2: i think it’s the perfect time for #fridayintroductions.  i was fishing through my photos to find a decent picture of myself
column3: but then i stopped and was like
column4: i should just snap one real quick selfie of me now.  the way i look at this moment
column5: at the end of the day
column7: in dire need of a haircut
column8: with sprouts always growing out of the top of my head.  this is me so
column11: married to my husband for 12 years
column12: and a mom of two lovely girls ages 10 and 7.  i’m 43 years old
column13: an infp on the meyers brigg and a 9 on the enneagram.  i am a former kindergarten teacher of 14 years.  i left my career after having my second child to stay at home with my girls.  i am now an independent distributor for young living and absolutely love what i do and so grateful that i can be at home to raise my girls.  things i love:  my family
column21: and the colors pink and aqua.  just like you
column22: i am not perfect.  i deal with anxiety
column26: and anger issues.  i’ve come a long way in some of these areas.  how you ask?  lots of god
column32: self care and a lot of grace.  i used to keep some of the above very private
column33: but i don’t anymore.  i remember when i was going through hard times
column34: feeling very alone and sometimes ashamed
column35: but became very encouraged when finding the very few people on social media going through similar experiences and sharing about it.  it was rare to find
column36: but so comforting to know that i wasn’t alone.  so if you’re going through something similar to me
column39: and i promise things do get better.  most importantly is that you are not alone. ❤️#godhasyourback #thisisme #yourenotalone #myforties;;en;#fridayintroductions.

column2: jag vägrar att stryka mansbebisen medhårs och genom det förminska hans sjuka beteende.

column3: en ny kvinna. en kvinna som sedan lämnade mansbebisen pga han inte brydde sig om sina barn! klok kvinna.

column1: men innan detta var jag i mansbebisen bostad för att låna internet och maila några jobbansökningar. ett av barnen
column2: knappt tio år var med mig. hen tittade på tv i mansbebisens vardagsrum. datorn stod i sovrummet.

column1: när jag var färdig och ansökningarna skickade roade sig mansbebisen med att knuffa ner mig i sängen där han snabbt satte sig på mig och lika fort satte han fast mina handleder i sängen. sängen som var preparerad med ett par handklovar. jag kunde inte komma loss. jag kunde inte skrika för barnet som satt i rummet intill. mansbebisen satt tungt på min bröstkorg. jag försökte sparka mot honom men av förklarliga skäl nådde jag inte honom. där sitter mansbebisen med sitt kön nära mitt ansikte och han knäpper upp sina byxor. vad som sedan hände vill jag inte skriva. det tar emot och jag skäms fast  intelligensen säger mig att det inte är jag som ska skämmas. det är han. inte jag. jag skäms pga de sjuka reaktioner jag fick från släktingar när jag väl lät detta ut i dagsljus.
hon vill bara göra honom illa."" eller så fick jag höra att sättet jag berättade på var fel. inte någon sa; men vad i helvete gjorde han?inte någon sa ett enda ord varken till stöd eller förståelse.
dum som jag var anmälde jag inte. jag tänkte på barnen och jag tänkte på mansbebisens föräldrar. jag tänkte inte på mig själv. från den dagen var inte mansbebisen välkommen i mitt och barnens hem.
jag gick till polisen för sent. brottet var nu preskriberat.
men jag fick veta av polisen att om jag anmält då så hade detta rubricerats som olaga frihetsberövande samt grov våldtäkt/våldtäkt och han hade dömts till fängelse.
en mansbebis med ny kvinna tyckte sig ha rätten att förgripa sig på sin före dettas kropp.

det är inte jag som ska skämmas. skammen ska placeras där den hör hemma. mina inlägg visar vem som faktiskt gjorde illa!";;en;#metoo;;;;;0;;mansbebisens_fru;Mansbebisens fru;;0;False;4;0;0;22;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/3481b5476081719a102c700713bbed25/5D16BEC8/t51.2885-15/e35/49279351_134198064257619_6658450189949921073_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"dagen jag aldrig kommer att glömma. jag är inte ensam om att ha råkat ut för likde händelser #metoo men jag vägrar att hålla tyst

column1: 89759;instagram;2019-01-05 06:36:53;FALSE;i was 7 years old and my whole world flipped upside down. i didn’t understand what was happening to me
column2: but i knew it was wrong. i had no one
column3: absolutely no one to go to. i was being sexually abused by a family member. someone who should have cared and nurtured me
column4: took advantage of me. it made me very scared and many other bad things for a very long time. it wasn’t until i was almost 30 that i let go of the hurt and pain and learned what forgiveness really is. to this day i still deal with the aftermath of the trauma. it’s an everyday struggle that i deal with anxiety
column5: depression and many other things. i share this story to bring awareness and the stigma of people not wanting to believe horrible things like this exist and can happen to anyone and i’m not trying to gain sympathy but an understanding. i hope by sharing my story and my truth will help someone else speak up and speak out against sexual abuse and eventually begin healing. love

column1: i am valid. i am all the things i once knew i was.
i will say this; the person causing this now was not the first to do so. perhaps my past is clouding up this puddle too.
years before they came to be in my life
column2: i was assaulted. assault has so many fucking layers. fear
column10: and so on. healing has no time frame
column11: and it can be easy to present yourself as healed to anyone you might have told. people believe the strong woman

column1: i have spent hours hating myself. hours convincing myself i caused it. hours telling myself that because i froze i must have wanted it. maybe i didn't say stop loud enough. maybe i didn't push him off hard enough. it is only recently that i was told (by a professional) that freezing is common. i wish i had known sooner. well really
column2: i wish i never had to know.
not completely healed but almost there. and then destruction.

column1: every sliver of doubt expanded with their words. their actions ripped what was left of my self worth apart. from the basic structure of my body to how i choose to mother my daughter was not only questioned but torn down by them.
i was left void. in a void? was a void.
these are the things i am beginning to see again

not completely healed but almost there. and then destruction.

column1: every sliver of doubt expanded with their words. their actions ripped what was left of my self worth apart. from the basic structure of my body to how i choose to mother my daughter was not only questioned but torn down by them.
i was left void. in a void? was a void.
these are the things i am beginning to see again
column2: that i am beginning to know again.

column3: took office on jan. 20. it failed
column4: with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

column1: 89975;instagram;2019-01-05 01:52:04;FALSE;"qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv
column2: completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

column1: that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing
column2: just part of the story we are all interacting with.

column1: the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters
column2: then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

column1: that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics
column3: and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters
column4: so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

column2: 2018. a lot of people came for me for citing the “fake news” about r kelly and his “harem” of young women. for coming for men of color. as though protecting a proven predator who is a man of color is a traitorous act. if you are a predator
column3: you are a predator. don’t talk to me about an intersectional approach to protecting celebrity men. but... this is not an “i told you so” but rather i’m hoping it’s an opportunity for people to recognize that yes it’s time to #unfriendanrkellysympathizer but this is not a time to be myopic and think it’s just r kelly. this is a pervasive problem of ingrained systemic sexual violence that disproportionately affects #youngwomenofcolor #girlsofcolor in its lack of visibility. original post below.

column1: i recently wrote an essay in which i talked about woc / girls of color and how our pain within the context of #metoo // #timesup // celebrity worship is largely ignored. i cited r kelly as a #caseandpoint example.
i’m glad to see that finally this example is being proven wrong. (hopefully)

but he’s not the only one. the rate at which woc // young woc // girls of color are sexually abused and destroyed is exhorbitantly and disproportionately high to the rate that we hear and do anything about it. we all know a survivor. i know i do.

r. kelly is a start. let’s follow up with some of the previously untouchable celebrities in positions of power who have used their race and economics and social standing to silence woc. and the trash men who aren’t famous. you don’t need to be a celebrity to act like this
column2: you also don’t need to be a celebrity to be prosecuted for these actions.
